5000|$|On February 28 and March 7, 2013 the {{judicial}} {{panel of the}} Bavarian parliament debated the causa Mollath. This particularly emphasised the question whether judge Otto Brixner had influenced tax fraud investigations. Roland Jüptner, president of the Bavarian state office for taxes (Bayerisches Landesamt für <b>Steuern),</b> denied this. During the first session, he based this opinion {{on the fact that}} if this actually was the case, there would be a remark in the files. German newspaper [...] "Süddeutsche Zeitung" [...] subsequently reported that such a remark in fact existed.|$|E
